00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:52,160
what we call edge functions. They need

273
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:54,440
caching, HTTPS, authentication, content

274
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:56,600
negotiation, rate limiting for security,

275
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:59,080
and so all this functionality at the API

276
00:08:56,600 --> 00:09:00,880
level it's pretty repetitive. So, having

277
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:03,520
to implement this both on the front-end

278
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:05,440
side and on the back-end side every time

279
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:08,120
we plug in a new microservice to the

280
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:10,320
micro front-end ends up adding a lot of

281
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:11,640
