285
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:20,360
that would be your gate into the

286
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:22,800
back-end systems. And the advantage of

287
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:25,280
an API gateway is that the client would

288
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:26,760
only implement the edge functions once.

289
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:29,520
So, they basically only implement the

290
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:31,520
HTTPS handshake once, or caching, or

291
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:33,040
rate limiting, and then once the request

292
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:34,760
goes to the API gateway, it gets

293
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:36,680
forwarded to the back-end services,

294
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:38,680
which don't have to care about all this

295
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:40,480
functionality. They can just care about

296
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:42,640
their own logic. And all this usually

297
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:44,400
lives in a virtual private cloud, which

298
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:46,280
means it's totally secure because the

299
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:48,360
only way to go into it is through the

300
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:49,960
API gateway. The other cool feature when

301
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:51,360
you have an API gateway is that you can

302
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:53,920
make the communication between the

303
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:55,320
client and API gateway HTTPS, but the

304
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:57,840
communication between the microservices

