00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:59,360
and the API gateway HTTP because you

306
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:01,400
don't need that security anymore cuz

307
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:03,680
you're in a closed environment. And the

308
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:06,280
advantage here is performance because

309
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:08,600
HTTPS it's likely less performant than

310
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:10,960
the HTTP because you need more round

311
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:12,200
trips to do the HTTPS handshake. So, in

312
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:13,640
general, once you have a couple of

313
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:15,440
microservices in production, it's a good

314
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:17,480
idea to add an API gateway both for

315
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:19,360
security and performance and also less

316
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:20,840
complexity in the front end. Now, let's

317
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:22,480
move on to our next pattern, very

318
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:23,920
similar to the API gateway, we have the

319
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:25,520
backend for frontend. Now, let's

320
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:27,440
remember our setup from before where we

321
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:30,080
have our client and our API gateway and

322
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:32,360
all our microservices. The problem here

323
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:34,240
is that the client has to make a call to

324
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:36,400
